<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The northern Brisbane suburb that investors and practical buyers pursue for its northern corridor location, Airport Link access, proximity to Westfield Chermside, and a price point that delivers real value in one of Brisbane's most active employment corridors.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Virginia sits approximately thirteen kilometres north of the Brisbane CBD, positioned in the northern residential and employment corridor between Chermside and the Brisbane Airport precinct. The suburb's character is a genuine mix: established residential streets sit alongside industrial and commercial activity in a configuration that reflects the suburb's evolution from a purely industrial zone to a more diverse suburb where owner-occupiers and investors coexist with commercial operators. Virginia Golf Club is the most prominent green space landmark in the suburb, and the residential pockets around the club and in the suburb's quieter streets attract families and owner-occupiers who value the northern corridor location without the price premium of Aspley or Chermside.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
