    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Airport Link gives Virginia residents efficient CBD access despite the suburb's northern position, and the Brisbane Airport precinct is a practical destination for workers who base their housing search around minimising that particular commute. Westfield Chermside, one of Brisbane's largest retail and dining destinations, is just to the south and provides the major retail amenity for the suburb. The northern employment corridor along the Bruce Highway adds further employment access that investors targeting rental demand understand well.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The housing stock in Virginia spans older detached homes on reasonable blocks, units, and townhouses. The investor buyer pool in Virginia is active and informed, and properties that present clearly and are priced correctly against recent comparable sales attract genuine inquiry from buyers who have done their analysis. Owner-occupier buyers, particularly those who work along the northern corridor or at the airport, add a second consistent demand layer to the market.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
