    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Virginia.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Virginia?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Virginia values are driven by the suburb's northern corridor location, Airport Link and Bruce Highway access, proximity to Westfield Chermside, and consistent investor demand from buyers targeting the suburb's solid rental yield profile. The accessible price point relative to Chermside and Aspley draws both investors and first home buyers. Properties in the residential pockets away from the industrial activity, particularly on established streets with family homes, attract the strongest owner-occupier competition.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Virginia?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Virginia homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The investor buyer pool is active and moves efficiently when a property meets its criteria. Owner-occupier buyers targeting the northern corridor add further demand depth. Correct pricing against recent comparable sales in Virginia, and awareness of what buyers are comparing it against in Aspley and Chermside, is the central factor in campaign speed and result quality.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Virginia?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Virginia offers a practical northern Brisbane lifestyle about thirteen kilometres from the CBD. Virginia Golf Club is the suburb's standout green space. Westfield Chermside is close to the south, Airport Link provides efficient CBD access, and the broader northern employment and airport corridor is the commute destination for many residents. The suburb rewards buyers who choose it for practical reasons: location, value, and proximity to northern Brisbane's major employment hubs.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Virginia a good suburb to invest in?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Virginia has consistently attracted investor interest for its combination of accessible price points, solid rental demand from the northern employment corridor, and proximity to the Brisbane Airport precinct and Westfield Chermside. The suburb's industrial-residential mix means the tenant base is diverse, and investors who understand the specific demand profile here make better decisions about what to buy, how to present it, and what rental outcome is realistic.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

